{{doc/start}}
Renders a sortable wikitable of recipes for an item or element, with columns for recipe name, inputs, outputs, craft time, and crafting building(s). Backed by [[Module:RecipeTable]].

Use [[Template:RecipeTable Building]] to show all recipes craftable in a specific building, or [[Template:RecipeTable Recipe]] to display a single recipe row by its identifier.

== Usage ==
<pre>
{{RecipeTable|_base_iron_ingot}}
{{RecipeTable|id=_base_iron_ingot|mode=producing}}
{{RecipeTable|id=_base_iron_ingot|mode=consuming}}
{{RecipeTable|id=_base_iron_ingot|mode=all}}
</pre>

== Parameters ==
{| class="wikitable"
! Parameter !! Description !! Type !! Status
|-
| <code>1</code> / <code>id</code> || Item or element template identifier (e.g. <code>_base_iron_ingot</code>). || String || Required
|-
| <code>mode</code> || Which recipes to show: <code>producing</code> (default) — recipes that output this item; <code>consuming</code> — recipes that consume it; <code>all</code> — both. || String || Optional
|}

== Notes ==
* Recipe data comes from [[Module:Data/Recipes]] and [[Module:Data/RecipeIndex]].
* Crafting buildings are resolved via [[Module:Data/RecipeBuildingNames]] and linked as <code>NAME (Building)</code>.
* Elemental inputs/outputs are shown with a litre (<code>L</code>) unit.
* The table is sortable by any column.
* If no matching recipes exist, the template outputs nothing.
{{doc/end}}
